Interview Questions
1) What are jump statements in Java?
-->Jump statements are used to transfer control of execution from one place to another.
      👉 Types:
            break
            continue
            return


2) What is the purpose of the break statement?
-->👉 Terminates loop or switch immediately.
      for(int i=1;i<=5;i++){
          if(i==3) break;
          System.out.println(i);
      }


3) What is the purpose of the continue statement?
-->👉 Skips current iteration and moves to next.
    for(int i=1;i<=5;i++){
        if(i==3) continue;
        System.out.println(i);
    }


4) What is the purpose of the return statement?
-->👉 Exits entire method and optionally returns value.

    return value;


5) Can we use break without a loop or switch?
-->❌ No → Compile-time error
    (Except labeled blocks, but not standalone)


6) Can we use continue in a switch statement? Why or why not?
-->❌ No  👉 Because continue is only for loops, not switch.


7) What is the difference between break and continue / return?
-->
| Feature | break       | continue        | return      |
| ------- | ----------- | --------------- | ----------- |
| Scope   | Loop/Switch | Loop only       | Method      |
| Effect  | Stops loop  | Skips iteration | Ends method |



8) Can break terminate a method in Java?
-->❌ No 👉 It only exits loop/switch, not method.


9) What will happen if you write multiple break statements in nested loops?
-->👉 Each break exits only the nearest loop


