      1) Write a program to check Armstrong number (e.g., 153 → 13+53+33=153).
      -->Armstrong Number
      public class Armstrong {
          public static void main(String[] args) {
              int num = 153, sum = 0, temp = num;
      
              while(temp > 0){


                  int digit = temp % 10;
                  sum += digit * digit * digit;
                  temp /= 10;
              }
      
              if(sum == num)
                  System.out.println("Armstrong");
              else
                  System.out.println("Not Armstrong");
          }
      }


2) How do you check if a number is a Strong Number using loops in Java?
-->Strong Number
    public class Strong {
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            int num = 145, sum = 0, temp = num;
    
            while(temp > 0){
                int digit = temp % 10;
                int fact = 1;
    
                for(int i=1;i<=digit;i++){
                    fact *= i;
                }
    
                sum += fact;
                temp /= 10;
            }
    
            System.out.println(sum == num ? "Strong" : "Not Strong");
        }
    }


